Details:
I wanted to lose some fat around my belly and thought they should be able to help since they say they have the best machines. I was already exercising 3 times per week and on a diet. They suggested two very expensive treatments, Emsculpt Neo for 24,000 pesos and PBR serums for 10,000 pesos, and also some medication, for about 6,000 total.
I went to the clinic for 3 months once per week for different treatments. During these 3 months, I listened to all of their instructions- I was on a diet, and I was exercising 4 or 5 times per week very heavily. As a result of the exercise (at a very good gym), all of my body changed, but the belly area had zero changes. I already knew that exercise and diet would not help me get rid of the belly fat since I know my body very well, that is why I agreed to pay 40,000 pesos for the services of this clinic, and I got zero result, and zero customer care, they didn't care AT ALL about their patient; and they did not try anything else, just said that this is my fault because I haven't exercised which I DID and it is very visible in the rest of my body.", 'languageCode': 'en'}, 'originalText': {'text': "Emsculpt Neo and PBR Serum review:

Terrible customer service too. Would not return nor recommend.

Had a good 90 min “relaxation massage with Jenny. So good that she convinced me to book a package of 5 (buy 4 get 1 free). I did and booked my 2nd massage for the week after with Jenny. Turn up and Jenny tells me she can’t do it (I don’t really understand why) and refers me to a colleague. I was disappointed as I only booked the package because of a good massage with Jenny but I tried the recommendation because she said if I was not happy I would have her again the week after. It was not a good massage, this one was distracted, texting, didn’t cover any areas of concern and no pressure AT ALL. It was very uncomfortable - couldn’t wait for it to be over. I had already paid in the package so just chalked it up to a bad experience and intended to just have Jenny after that so I wasn’t in that position again! When I came to book my 3rd appt I book with Jenny again, working around her availability. However, on the day of the massage I was told she is not available, again. I specifically chose a day and time around Jenny’s availability so this was frustrating. This time I do not want to have yet another new therapist so I ask for a refund on the remaining 2 massages if I can not book with Jenny (understanding I lose the free one) as she isn’t available and I didn’t enjoy the last replacement. Well that’s when it was very clear that their customer service is not good!! Took me ENDLESS chats with different people over 3 days to get any of my money back. Despite the therapist I wanted not being available AFTER being booked in (twice), not being happy with their replacement and not having 3 of the 5 massages on the package they did not think I should get the cost of just 2 massages back. They only gave me a partial refund after much painful debate (and kept 600 pesos for “taxes”). It was a horrible experience. I would never return purely on this basis and wanted to caution others. They could have handled it so much better and simply apologised for the change of availability and refunded.  It would be then be my choice if I wanted to try someone new and pay again. I certainly wouldn’t pay for 5 upfront because you likely won’t get the therapist you book with and you will be trapped into paying for something you don’t want and not reimbursed if they can’t provide what you booked. Very disappointing from what was initially a nice experience. They encourage you to buy a package and then they don’t care once they have your money upfront because they won’t return it if there’s an issue!

Also interesting that after all this and not returning my money for the massages not taken (I still paid for the terrible one of course!), they offer me a free massage out of nowhere. This was so strange after they had been rude all week and held on to my money. Obviously not a massage anyone would take by that point so very much too little too late! Presumably this was so they can pretend they gave good customer service. For the sake of keeping 600 pesos, they lost a regular client. Despite the therapist I wanted not being available AFTER being booked in (twice), not being happy with their replacement and not having 3 of the 5 massages on the package they did not think I should get the cost of just 2 massages back. They only gave me a partial refund after much painful debate (and kept 600 pesos for “taxes”). It was a horrible experience. I would never return purely on this basis and wanted to caution others. They could have handled it so much better and simply apologised for the change of availability and refunded.  It would be then be my choice if I wanted to try someone new and pay again. I certainly wouldn’t pay for 5 upfront because you likely won’t get the therapist you book with and you will be trapped into paying for something you don’t want and not reimbursed if they can’t provide what you booked. Very disappointing from what was initially a nice experience. They encourage you to buy a package and then they don’t care once they have your money upfront because they won’t return it if there’s an issue!

Also interesting that after all this and not returning my money for the massages not taken (I still paid for the terrible one of course!), they offer me a free massage out of nowhere. This was so strange after they had been rude all week and held on to my money. Obviously not a massage anyone would take by that point so very much too little too late! Presumably this was so they can pretend they gave good customer service. For the sake of keeping 600 pesos, they lost a regular client. I traveled approximately 7 hours (including transportation in each city) because I saw everything they were doing on TikTok and there was an undeniable energy that attracted me not to miss the experience. I went with the reason to give him an early birthday gift. It was my great surprise, and above all delight, that it is not just something you see through the camera, it is real.

From the beginning, when talking to Pame about my personal situation, she was totally attentive, she didn't miss a single detail and you can instantly notice the level of professionalism. The advice was impeccable, provided by both her and Sof, one of her stylists, who was the one who gave me the hair washing and detangling prior to the cut. The atmosphere is so relaxing and pleasant, I was able to relax among the daily chaos. And when Pame moved on to give me the cut, I mentioned that I wanted my face to be clear and keep the length as long as possible, otherwise I gave her creative freedom.

The cut was incredible. Additionally, I want to thank you very much for the detail you showed me, it is honestly something that I will never forget and you can count on my loyalty from now on, even if you are far away from me hahaha.

Note: I bought the shampoo and conditioner, I am still slowly using them and seeing the change slowly, I will update this review when my hair heals to address it properly.

A hug and keep it up ", 'languageCode': 'en-US'}, 'originalText': {'text': 'Simplemente increíble.

Viajé aproximádamente 7 horas (incluyendo transporte en cada ciudad) porque vi todo lo que estaban haciendo en TikTok y había una energía innegable que me atraía a no perderme de la experiencia. Yo fui con el motivo de regalármelo de cumpleaños adelantado. Fue mi gran sorpresa, y sobre todo deleite, que no es solamente algo que veas a través de la cámara, es real.

Desde el principio, al conversar con Pame sobre mi situación personal, fue totalmente atenta, no perdió ni un solo detalle y puedes notar el nivel de profesionalismo al instante. La asesoría fue impecable, brindada tanto por ella como por Sof, una de sus estilistas, quien fue la que me otorgó el lavado de cabello y desenredado previo al corte. El ambiente es tan relajante y ameno, pude relajarme entre el caos cotidiano. Y cuando Pame prosiguió a hacerme el corte, le mencioné que quería que mi cara estuviera despejada y mantuviera el largo lo más posible, de lo demás le daba libertad creativa.

[{'name': 'places/ChIJRaWv7R0C0oURdv2qKXWABPo/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNYbnM3S19BRRAB', 'relativePublishTimeDescription': '5 months ago', 'rating': 5, 'text': {'text': "Great experience and we will stay at this hotel our next time in Mexico City! Very clean hotel throughout, including our room being cleaned thoroughly daily. Luxurious bathroom and comfortable bed, along with a big TV which was nice to watch movies on, with a really nice leather couch and dining table setup (kitchen is good sized!). Only critique about the room would be a request to upgrade the blow dryer and outlets; blow dryer is a cheap, old model was sticky with hair product (I'm guessing) from previous use over time, and the outlet in the bathroom is so loose it barely holds a plug in place.

Used the gym 4 out of 6 mornings; gym is a little small, but has everything you need to get a good and full body workout. Hope they upgrade the gym equipment in the near future though, as the cable machine is a little dated. Would be nice to have floors that were rubber, rather than wood floors which the benches slide on. Great gym for a hotel, overall!

Also used the steam room and sauna all 6 mornings, and those were great to conveniently have access to. The hot tub was always clean, and we used the pool a few times.

Staff was VERY nice, attentive, and professional. They are so nice and informative when we asked for restaurant suggestions and etc. Felt valued as a guest at their hotel.

Lastly, daily (free) breakfast was amazing! They had different options each day we were there, and the food was super good. 2. OSCAR (waiter) hands down the best, most polite and professional waiter in the hotel. He should be training all the other waiter staff on how to look after the customers. In the case of the showers, well, yes, because then they close half of them and then you have to wait a little while.

In general it is good, very equipped.

On Friday and Saturday it is not 24 hours, they close at 1 am on Friday and open at 6 am, Saturday and Sunday it is from 6 am to 11 pm.

If you arrive through the parking lot access, after 12 they ask you to show your code.', 'languageCode': 'en-US'}, 'originalText': {'text': 'Las instalaciones, limpias, el personal atento, siempre voy después de las 00:30 porque hay poca gente, esta última semana he visto filas y que ya no está tan vacío despues de esa hora, de todos modos se pueden entrenar prácticamente sin detenerse.

Para el caso de las regaderas pues ahí si, porque luego cierran la mitad y entonces luego toca esperar un ratito.

En general está bien, muy equipado.

Los viernes y sábado no es 24 hrs, cierran a la 1 am del viernes y abren a las 6 am, sábado y domingo es de 6am a 11 pm.

Si llegas por el acceso del estacionamiento, después de las 12 te piden que enseñes tu código.', 'languageCode': 'es'}, 'authorAttribution': {'displayName': 'Jose Alberto', 'uri': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109959752397810253554/reviews', 'photoUri': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWXJNaz3DAvcgKOIrqhuGraJqIDbsoEMPD-7R4ArRWNr8FETop1Nw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4'}, 'publishTime': '2024-07-23T14:42:13.237232Z', 'flagContentUri': 'https://www.google.com/local/review/rap/report?postId=ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNqck15SzJ3RRAB&d=17924085&t=1', 'googleMapsUri': 'https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNqck15SzJ3RRAB!2m1!1s0x85d1f99e560f3883:0xc8d465d7c99061ad'}]

No.  Mostly, they are looking for the next scam and pay little attention to you once you actually hire a massage.  Gave up on the group and switched to private.  And again, the game is to get as much money from you while doing the least.  Yes, they will promise they know how, demand a lot, settle on a price and then ... maybe they show - an hour, two hours later.  Literally.  Or they begin (having shown they know pretty much nothing about the body) and immediately start to complain and give up 15 min in - their tired. I am very dissatisfied with the services of this clinic. Spent more than 40,000 pesos and got zero result, and zero customer satisfaction, they just didn't care...

Details:
I wanted to lose some fat around my belly and thought they should be able to help since they say they have the best machines. I was already exercising 3 times per week and on a diet. They suggested two very expensive treatments, Emsculpt Neo for 24,000 pesos and PBR serums for 10,000 pesos, and also some medication, for about 6,000 total.
I went to the clinic for 3 months once per week for different treatments. During these 3 months, I listened to all of their instructions- I was on a diet, and I was exercising 4 or 5 times per week very heavily. As a result of the exercise (at a very good gym), all of my body changed, but the belly area had zero changes. I already knew that exercise and diet would not help me get rid of the belly fat since I know my body very well, that is why I agreed to pay 40,000 pesos for the services of this clinic, and I got zero result, and zero customer care, they didn't care AT ALL about their patient; and they did not try anything else, just said that this is my fault because I haven't exercised which I DID and it is very visible in the rest of my body.", 'languageCode': 'en'}, 'originalText': {'text': "Emsculpt Neo and PBR Serum review:

I just enrolled in December 2023, and I wasn't sure I could endure a month. Now, four months later, I'm discovering new limits.

reviews:
[{'name': 'places/ChIJ63g_DIL_0YUR9a8lFxyUBzE/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUM3cGJLbndBRRAB', 'relativePublishTimeDescription': '7 months ago', 'rating': 2, 'text': {'text': "I visited this spa today without an appointment, and it was a bit challenging to find as it's located in a very discreet spot with no visible signage. This made me realize the importance of scheduling an appointment in advance.

Upon arrival, despite not having an appointment, I was directed to a very small room at the front of the building. The room was so cramped that it barely had any space to move around. When given the choice, I opted for the basic oil massage. However, without my consent, my massage was upgraded to the more advanced option, which I did not request.

Unfortunately, my masseuse was on her menstrual period, which affected the overall experience. Given the situation, I would have preferred to stick with the basic massage, as the upgrade was unnecessary. Additionally, there was a noticeable odor that made the experience uncomfortable.

There were also no linens on the massage table or on the futon couch in the already cramped room. I strongly recommend that they consider adding more linens to their furniture. Moreover, I was not given the opportunity to shower before the massage, which would have been appreciated.

In summary, the massage itself was decent, but the overall experience could have been much better with a few adjustments. Allowing customers time to shower, offering more comfortable rooms, and respecting their choices regarding upgrades would significantly improve the experience.", 'languageCode': 'en'}, 'originalText': {'text': "I visited this spa today without an appointment, and it was a bit challenging to find as it's located in a very discreet spot with no visible signage. While not high-end, all the desserts we bought were delicious, and the bread was a rustic multigrain that went great with soup.

That said… this is not your normal bakery. Coming here in the afternoon will feel like a free-for-all. Maybe a hundred fellow shoppers running around collecting and paying. Tables stacked high with foods. It looks like pure chaos.

If you’ve never been before, the order of operations is to grab a large silver tray and your own tongs. Run around stacking all the baked goods you want.

Next, you go to the area where folks are packaging. You drop off your tray and get handed a ticket. They’ll package it and wrap it into either parchment paper or boxes.

With the ticket, you head over to pay. This is usually the longest lineup. Allegedly they take credit card, but I’ve never managed to get it to work and having cash is your best bet.

Finally, after paying, you’ll get a receipt and ticket. Take both back to the person who packed your baked goods. Congrats, you did it.

It’s a unique experience and once complete, you’ll be heading out with kilos of pastry. Amazing. Prices are about 10-20 pesos per pastry, and about 20 peso for a loaf of bread.

Oh yeah, no helpful English-speaking staff. They’ve got enough locals to process that there’s no time for us tourists. Hopefully my guide above is helpful.', 'languageCode': 'en'}, 'originalText': {'text': 'This massive, factory-sized bakery provides every type of pastry, bread, and cake you’d want at extremely inexpensive prices. Next, you go to the area where folks are packaging. You drop off your tray and get handed a ticket. They’ll package it and wrap it into either parchment paper or boxes.

With the ticket, you head over to pay. This is usually the longest lineup. Allegedly they take credit card, but I’ve never managed to get it to work and having cash is your best bet.

Finally, after paying, you’ll get a receipt and ticket. Take both back to the person who packed your baked goods. Congrats, you did it.

It’s a unique experience and once complete, you’ll be heading out with kilos of pastry. Amazing. Prices are about 10-20 pesos per pastry, and about 20 peso for a loaf of bread.

Oh yeah, no helpful English-speaking staff. They’ve got enough locals to process that there’s no time for us tourists. reviews:
[{'name': 'places/ChIJ20CftNQDzoUR51XvHigI9PE/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURRXzlmZ0lREAE', 'relativePublishTimeDescription': 'in the last week', 'rating': 2, 'text': {'text': "**Title: Security Guards Harassment**

I visited this mall several times last week, and each visit was marred by harassment from security guards, especially near the taxi/Uber pick-up area. I had dental work done, spending over $1,500, which underscores that I was a paying customer, not loitering. After a tiring gym session, I took a moment to rest while waiting for my ride.

Despite not obstructing anyone, the guards approached me repeatedly. First, I was told I couldn't lean against the walls. I complied, only to be told that kneeling down was not allowed. After moving again, I found a spot to sit for the five minutes it took for my Uber to arrive, but they approached me once more and said I couldn’t sit down either. This behavior extended to other individuals, including workers on their lunch break who were simply trying to rest while working on mall signs.

When I asked the guards why they felt the need to keep harassing me, they expressed their own frustration, stating they were compelled by their bosses to do so or risk losing their jobs. Seeking clarity, I approached the administration office to file a complaint about this absurd treatment. Their response? Excuses about “safety” concerns and the risk of electrocution from wires inside the support beams, while dismissing my valid concerns.

I told them that if this was true, the mall needed to be closed to the public while this problem was fixed. The two women I spoke with seemed displeased by my presence and did provide a complaint form, but it’s unclear if any real action will be taken. This experience was disappointing and discouraging for those of us trying to spend money at the mall. I hope improvements will be made to prevent this kind of harassment in the future.", 'languageCode': 'en'}, 'originalText': {'text': "**Title: Security Guards Harassment**

I had a 5k hair transplant at Dreo, and the experience was exceptional. The team was attentive, providing pickup and drop-off services, and their attention to detail during the surgery was outstanding. I appreciated how the staff seemed genuinely happy to be there—they sang and made the atmosphere relaxed, which helped ease my nerves.

While 5k grafts are a significant procedure and I did experience some facial swelling despite following post-op care instructions, the overall experience was worth it. I chose the VIP package and decided to arrive early in CDMX and stay an extra week after the procedure because this transplant is important to me.

I visited several clinics across the USA, Thailand, Colombia, and even Mexico (including ones in Cancún), but my decision wasn’t based on price. It was the pre- and post-operative care that made Dreo stand out. I definitely recommend this place for anyone considering a hair transplant.

I traveled approximately 7 hours (including transportation in each city) because I saw everything they were doing on TikTok and there was an undeniable energy that attracted me not to miss the experience. I went with the reason to give him an early birthday gift. It was my great surprise, and above all delight, that it is not just something you see through the camera, it is real.

From the beginning, when talking to Pame about my personal situation, she was totally attentive, she didn't miss a single detail and you can instantly notice the level of professionalism. The advice was impeccable, provided by both her and Sof, one of her stylists, who was the one who gave me the hair washing and detangling prior to the cut. The atmosphere is so relaxing and pleasant, I was able to relax among the daily chaos. And when Pame moved on to give me the cut, I mentioned that I wanted my face to be clear and keep the length as long as possible, otherwise I gave her creative freedom.

The cut was incredible. Additionally, I want to thank you very much for the detail you showed me, it is honestly something that I will never forget and you can count on my loyalty from now on, even if you are far away from me hahaha.

Note: I bought the shampoo and conditioner, I am still slowly using them and seeing the change slowly, I will update this review when my hair heals to address it properly.

A hug and keep it up ", 'languageCode': 'en-US'}, 'originalText': {'text': 'Simplemente increíble.

Viajé aproximádamente 7 horas (incluyendo transporte en cada ciudad) porque vi todo lo que estaban haciendo en TikTok y había una energía innegable que me atraía a no perderme de la experiencia. Yo fui con el motivo de regalármelo de cumpleaños adelantado. Fue mi gran sorpresa, y sobre todo deleite, que no es solamente algo que veas a través de la cámara, es real.

Desde el principio, al conversar con Pame sobre mi situación personal, fue totalmente atenta, no perdió ni un solo detalle y puedes notar el nivel de profesionalismo al instante. La asesoría fue impecable, brindada tanto por ella como por Sof, una de sus estilistas, quien fue la que me otorgó el lavado de cabello y desenredado previo al corte. El ambiente es tan relajante y ameno, pude relajarme entre el caos cotidiano. Y cuando Pame prosiguió a hacerme el corte, le mencioné que quería que mi cara estuviera despejada y mantuviera el largo lo más posible, de lo demás le daba libertad creativa.

El corte quedó increíble. Adicional, quiero agradecerle demasiado por el detalle que tuvo conmigo, sinceramente es algo que jamás voy a olvidar y puedes contar con mi lealtad de ahora en adelante, aunque me quedes muy lejos jajaja.

I had used hyaluronic acid in other clinics without problems, but decided to try this place two years ago based on a recommendation.

From the beginning, the treatment of the professional who applied the treatment to me was poor. There was no proper introduction or clear explanation of the procedure, which made me uneasy.

After the treatment, I experienced bruising, which had never happened to me before. Additionally, the underside of my eyelid became swollen, possibly due to a reaction to the acid. The most worrying thing is that, even though more than two years have passed, the inflammation has not disappeared.

My main concern is that possibly low quality material was used, which could have caused this adverse reaction. I hope that the dermatology center takes measures to improve the quality of its services and materials.', 'languageCode': 'en-US'}, 'originalText': {'text': 'Desafortunadamente, mi experiencia en este centro dermatológico fue muy decepcionante. Desde el principio, el trato del profesional que me aplicó el tratamiento fue deficiente. No hubo una introducción adecuada ni explicación clara del procedimiento, lo que me generó inquietud.

Después del tratamiento, experimenté moretones, lo cual nunca me había pasado antes. Además, la parte inferior del párpado se me inflamó, posiblemente debido a una reacción al ácido. Lo más preocupante es que, a pesar de que han pasado más de dos años, la inflamación no ha desaparecido.
